                    <para>In order to minimize confusion, it is imperative that each dealer checks via DDEW each VIN
                        with a "WPID" look up. The screen will display - by VIN, each campaign or AFC that should be
                        completed. If you have questions about how to conduct a WPID inquiry, please contact your TSM.
                        Dealership warranty administrators are conversant with this inquiry shown on page 11 of the
                        Service &#38; Warranty Dealer handbook.
                    </para>
                    <para>IN SUMMARY: What you should do now:</para>
                    <seqlist style="arabic">
                        <item>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">Review</emph>
                                each of the above campaigns with all Service personnel that contact customers.
                            </para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">Inform</emph>
                                key people - where the letters are filed at the dealership and how to perform WPID
                                inquiries.
                            </para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">Stock parts</emph>in minimum quantities based on vehicles in service
                                in your AOR.
                            </para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">Confirm</emph>
                                the rules for your dealership to ensure that these campaigns are communicated
                                consistently to customers.
                            </para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">Advise</emph>
                                other personnel at your dealership (parts and sales) how you plan to manage these
                                issues.
                            </para>
                        </item>
                    </seqlist>
                    <para>Please be progressive in your actions regarding these issues.</para>
                </lev1>
                <lev1>
                    <title>Replacement of Right Side Door View Window</title>
                    <para>Navistar has improved the door view window with a vented design for production and has
                        implemented a program to retrofit the non-vented view window with the new design in 5000
                        <emph type="italic">i</emph>
                        and 9000
                        <emph type="italic">i</emph>
                        Models built on or before July 26, 1999.
                    </para>
